TO HAVE AND TO HOLD the same, together with the rights and appurtenances thereto
belonging, unto Contractor and its successors and assigns, forever; provided, however, that the
obligations of Contractor hereunder shall continue regardless of any such sale or transfer; and
Contractor, for and in consideration of the Bank's agreement to advance the Loan Amount in
accordance with and subject to the terms of the Tri-Party Agreement, the receipt and sufficiency
of which is hereby acknowledged, hereby SELLS, TRANSFERS, ASSIGNS, GRANTS and
CONVEYS unto Bank, its successors and assigns, the said mechanic's, materialman's,
contractor's and laborer's liens herein given and granted as security for the payment of the Note,
together with all other rights and equities of Contractor hereunder. Payment of the Note also
shall be secured by the lien of the Deed of Trust that renews and extends the liens created by this
Contract.
To the extent, if any, that the Contract Sum exceeds the Loan Amount, then Contractor,
for the same consideration aforesaid, hereby expressly subordinates any and all liens of
Contractor (constitutional, statutory, contractual or otherwise) to the liens held or to be held by
Bank securing payment of the Note.
6.
PartialLien. Should the improvements to be constructed hereunder fail for any
reason to be completed or should all of the labor and materials to be used in the construction
thereof fail to be provided by Contractor, then Contractor or other holder of the hereinabove
mentioned indebtedness and Note shall have a valid and subsisting lien for the full Contract Sum
less such sum of money as will be reasonably required to complete said improvements in
accordance with the provisions hereof; or in such event the owner and holder of the Note, at its
option, shall have the right, but not the obligation, to complete said improvements, and the liens
herein given shall inure to the benefit of said owner and holder.
7.
Payments to Contractor. Payments to Contractor by Owner hereunder shall be
made in such manner and pursuant to such schedule as may be approved by Bank, as provided in
the Tri-Party Agreement. Notwithstanding anything in this Contract to the contrary, (a) During
construction and for thirty-one (31) days after completion of improvements, Owner may retain or
instruct Lender's designated Escrow Agent to retain ten percent (10%) of the Contract Sum or ten
percent (10%) of the value of the work performed by the Contractor; (b) If Owner might become
liable for a lien or claim for labor or materials furnished to Contractor and primarily chargeable
to Contractor, Owner may retain from payments on the Promissory Note from Owner to Lender
an amount sufficient to completely indemnify Owner against the lien or claim; (c) If Owner
elects not to retain funds for thirty-one (31) days, Owner and Contractor agree to and do hereby
hold Lender, its successors and assigns harmless from any and all loss, damage and expense,
including but not limited to attorney's fees, court costs and any and all costs of litigation, as well
as claims or causes of action, however characterized, larising from the failure to retain such
funds.
8.
Quality of Work. Contractor represents and warrants to Owner that the work shall
be completed in accordance with the Plans. Contractor shall, at its sole expense, make all
necessary repairs, replacements and corrections of any nature or description, interior or exterior,
